task.summary: Default task
Set up the event dispatcher
Added create events and the ability to register new objects.
Implemented the camera's basic existence
Added root object
Did stuff, things happened.
Added global scope loading and level scope loading (which is not called anywhere yet).
Added level scope loading and some simple wrappers around resource objects.
Added section tags having values and added a parent game object.
Added being able to get a list of instances.
Added deletion and infrastructure for despawning.
Added despawning, visiblility and disabling. (that took a while) Also added using pymedia as a backup when AVbin fails.
Changed from pyglet's event dispatcher to my own event dispatcher. Started adding layers.
Added layer movement based on hspeed and vspeed.
Added layer movement based on hspeed and vspeed.
Got bounding box collisions working! (in a non-brute force way)
Separated the collision system's instance grid into another module so that I can use it for the engine's other systems.
Got the visibility and activity systems to use the new hash grid format for checking.
Separated rendering into its own module and added batched sprite rendering. Rendering is now super efficient.
Fixed objects not appearing for one frame once onscreen.
